6 An Act relating to child custody; requiring notice to
custodial parent of in-patient treatment of
7 noncustodial parent; providing for codification; and
providing an effective date.
8
9
10 BE IT ENACTED BY THE PEOPLE OF THE STATE OF OKLAHOMA:
11 SECTION 1. NEW LAW A new section of law to be codified
12 in the Oklahoma Statutes as Section 4-107b of Title 43A, unless
13 there is created a duplication in numbering, reads as follows:
14 A custodial parent under a court order entered pursuant to the
15 provisions of Title 43 of the Oklahoma Statutes shall receive notice
16 from the noncustodial parent, or the noncustodial parent’s
17 representative if such parent is unable, if the noncustodial parent
18 is unable to comply with court-ordered visitation or any other
19 court-ordered requirement because he or she is receiving in-patient
20 treatment at a facility within the Department of Mental Health and
21 Substance Abuse Services or a facility certified by the Department.
22 SECTION 2. This act shall become effective November 1, 2025.
